A bombing in  Turkey  yesterday that
killed one policeman outside a security headquarters in Kayseri
was claimed by the Kurdistan Workersâ€™ Party, or PKK, the Firat
news agency reported.  The PKK, which is listed as a terrorist organization by
Turkey, the U.S. and the European Union, has been fighting for
autonomy in the southeast since 1984 in a conflict that has
claimed more than 40,000 lives.  To contact the reporter on this story:
